Eskom says it was planning a foreign bond sale and that the firm’s chief executive and Treasury team were currently on a road show overseas meeting with investors. JOHANNESBURG - Struggling state-owned power firm Eskom  offered investors up to $1.5 billion of 10-year bonds on Thursday, a source familiar with the matter said. Separately, Eskom spokesman Khulu Phasiwe said Eskom was planning a foreign bond sale and that the firm’s chief executive and Treasury team were currently on a road show overseas meeting with investors.